text:
A comfortable Coffee Shop ☕️  serving the
Heartlanders residing in Eunos Cresent as well as the workers near Ubi Industrial Park.
Serving:  Evergreen 🌲 😍: Hainanese Chicken Rice 🍚 😋,  Cai Png, Western Food
Noodles 🍜  with fish 🐟  balls or slices of
fish plus Zhi Char [serving Hot 🔥  Cooked
Teochew Style  Food ....seafood or fried].

Nice and clean environment Coffeeshop in Ubi.  Wide selections of local cuisines to choose from.  Teow Chew Noodles, Chinese Nasi Lemak, Western Food, Zi Cha, Duck Rice & Kway Chap and Mixed Rice Stalls all look real good!
Love this eatery. Quiet part of Eunos crescent. Breezy and not crowded like the coffeeshops near the market. 2 good halal stalls (western and tze char chinese style)
Nice good selection of food that nested the corner of the block. Very airy and cooling even though on a hot afternoon. Nice kopi with glass jelly! Will try the other stalls.

This is one of my favourite Yong tau foo stalls in Singapore. Their soup is light but has enough flavour to consider it proper soup, unlike many other Yong tau foo stalls I have tried. They do fry some of the ingredients for you and would ask what ingredients do you prefer to fry or add to the soup.
